<article class="env-convention" id="000H">
  <p><a class="environment-identifier" href="/tag/000H">Convention <span data-tag="000H">1.3.1</span>.</a> We will frequently use graphical presentation of morphisms in a monoidal category, representing a morphism $\varphi \colon A_1\otimes \dots \otimes A_ k\to B_1\otimes \dots \otimes B_ m$ by a box with $k$ inputs at the top and $m$ outputs at the bottom: </p>
  <p><figure class="figure">
  <div class="centered"><img class="includegraphics" src="/static/figures/fig05.svg" /> <figcaption class="figcaption">Figure 1.1. Graphical notation for a morphism in a monoidal category.</figcaption>  </div>

</figure></p>
</article>